FBIS3-25516 "drafr035_e_94003" FBIS-AFR-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 WEST AFRICA Nigeria Military Spokesman Denies Incursion Into Cameroon AB2202170794 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 1500 GMT 22 Feb 94 AB2202170794 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The Armed Forces have denied reports that Nigeria has carried out an incursion into Cameroonian territory. The director of defense information, Brigadier General Fred Chijuka, told newsmen in Lagos today that Nigerian forces [word indistinct] never [word indistinct] (?state of war) with Cameroon. He said an incident (?did occur) when Cameroonian gendarmes, out of pride, fired into a Nigerian convoy of troops. Brig. Gen. Chijuka said Cameroon merely embarked on malicious propaganda against Nigeria to gain undeserved sympathy from the international community. [passage indistinct]
